{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Generate Tests from Codebase",
  "description": "Scans the app's source code (Compose, SwiftUI, XML layouts), identifies screens, interactive elements, and user flows, then generates reusable YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder with cross-platform support.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Scan the mobile app source code in this workspace. Find all UI source files — look for: Kotlin Compose (*.kt with @Composable), SwiftUI (*.swift with View protocol/body), XML layouts (res/layout/*.xml), UIKit storyboards/xibs. For each screen found: 1) Identify all interactive elements (TextField, Button, Checkbox, Toggle, etc.) with their accessibility labels — for Compose: contentDescription/testTag; for SwiftUI: accessibilityIdentifier/accessibilityLabel; for XML: android:contentDescription. 2) Identify user flows (what happens on tap, state changes, navigation). 3) Determine platform based on source language — Kotlin/XML → android; Swift → ios; if both exist → [android, ios]. 4) Generate YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder following the schema in the generate-from-codebase steering file. Set the platform field correctly per script. 5) Generate e2e-tests/coverage.yaml listing all elements found and which are covered. 6) Generate e2e-tests/version.yaml with metadata. Output a summary of how many screens found, elements identified, platforms detected, and test scripts generated."
  }
}